%N A081757 Number of ways to write n as i*j+i-j, 0<i<j<=n.
%C A081757 For n > 1, a(n) is the number of divisors of n-1 that are strictly smaller than floor(sqrt(n-1)). - _Daniel Suteu_, May 14 2026
%H A081757 Reinhard Zumkeller, <a href="/A081757/b081757.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%F A081757 G.f.: x * Sum_{n >= 1} x^(n^2+3*n)/(1-x^n). - _Vladeta Jovovic_, May 13 2008 [Corrected by _Sean A. Irvine_, Nov 09 2025]
%e A081757 n=25 = 2*23+2-23 = 3*11+3-11 = 4*7+4-7, therefore a(25)=3.
%o A081757 (Haskell)
%o A081757 a081757 n = length [() | j <- [2..n], i <- [1..j-1], i * j + i - j == n]
%o A081757 -- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, May 24 2013
%o A081757 (PARI) a(n) = if(n<=1, return(0)); my(t=sqrtint(n-1)); #select(d->d<t,divisors(n-1)); \\ _Daniel Suteu_, May 14 2026
